This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR) techniques to predict the factuality and bias of news media sources. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category as it deals with NLP. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper uses IR techniques to extract features from news media sources. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) are also possible sub-categories as the paper uses information from social media and web traffic to predict the factuality and bias of news media sources. Finally, cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with identifying fake news and misinformation, which is a cybersecurity concern.
